01:04:42.278 --> 01:04:45.179
- Unusual.
- Unusual?

01:04:45.281 --> 01:04:47.340
-And bright.
- Ofcourse they're bright.

01:05:00.463 --> 01:05:02.624
I love this bit there.

01:05:28.658 --> 01:05:30.626
Miss Frame?

01:05:32.662 --> 01:05:34.630
Oh, there you are.

01:05:36.699 --> 01:05:38.997
Are you coming to morning tea?

01:05:40.102 --> 01:05:43.936
Oh - Oh, uh, no.
I'm a bit busy.

01:05:44.040 --> 01:05:47.806
Oh. We never see you.

01:05:49.211 --> 01:05:51.179
Maybe tomorrow.

01:05:53.716 --> 01:05:56.014
Oh, you've made the room lovely.

01:06:13.102 --> 01:06:16.003
So this was how it was...

01:06:16.105 --> 01:06:19.131
face to face with the future.

01:06:19.241 --> 01:06:21.300
Living apart from Isabel...

01:06:21.410 --> 01:06:23.776
pretending that I was not alone...

01:06:23.879 --> 01:06:27.508
and that teaching was what
I'd longed to do all my life.

01:06:29.618 --> 01:06:32.314
- Izzy! Isabel!
- What did they say?

01:06:32.421 --> 01:06:35.322
- Izzy!
- Have you heard about the bomb?

01:06:35.424 --> 01:06:37.824
- What bomb?
- They dropped a bomb on Japan!

01:06:37.927 --> 01:06:39.827
- They've killed millions of Japanese!

01:06:39.929 --> 01:06:42.557
- It's a new kind of bomb!
- So have we won the war?

01:06:42.665 --> 01:06:45.293
- Yes!
- Let's go tell the others!

01:06:46.469 --> 01:06:48.369
Coming?

01:06:49.972 --> 01:06:52.941
- Isabel, come on!
- Where did you hear it?

01:07:21.871 --> 01:07:26.171
We have a very important visitor
with us today, Second Class.

01:07:26.275 --> 01:07:30.905
I'd like you to say good morning
to our inspector, Mr. Niles.

01:07:31.013 --> 01:07:34.414
Good morning, Mr. Niles.

01:07:34.517 --> 01:07:36.917
Good morning, children.
Good, thanks.

01:07:37.019 --> 01:07:39.920
- And how are you, Miss Frame?
- Very well, thank you.

01:07:40.022 --> 01:07:43.423
That's good. I'll sit at the back,
and you just carry on as normal.

01:07:43.526 --> 01:07:45.494
Forget I'm here.

01:08:53.028 --> 01:08:55.258
What's she doing?

01:09:08.377 --> 01:09:11.938
M-Mr Niles, would you
excuse me for a minute, please?

01:09:12.046 --> 01:09:14.607
Certainly, Miss Frame.

01:11:19.375 --> 01:11:21.809
What about teaching?

01:11:22.678 --> 01:11:24.908
I've given it up.

01:11:25.014 --> 01:11:27.448
I've got a doctor's certificate.

01:11:27.549 --> 01:11:30.518
But you've always wanted
to be a teacher.

01:11:31.754 --> 01:11:35.281
- I'm going to be a writer.
- But how will you earn money?

01:11:40.462 --> 01:11:43.659
- How will you live?
- I'll work here in the kitchen.

01:11:43.766 --> 01:11:47.293
- I'll study psych at university.
- What about your scholarship?

01:11:49.605 --> 01:11:51.539
What about Mum and Dad?

01:12:00.449 --> 01:12:02.576
I can't believe it.

01:12:16.532 --> 01:12:19.057
I really enjoyed
your autobiography, Janet.

01:12:19.168 --> 01:12:22.399
It's very natural.
It's got a nice flow to it.

01:12:22.504 --> 01:12:24.972
The others were all
so stiff and serious.

01:12:25.074 --> 01:12:27.065
You've got a real talent for writing.

01:12:28.277 --> 01:12:30.802
I've had a story published
in The Listener.

01:12:30.913 --> 01:12:33.643
Oh. So I'm not wrong then.

01:12:38.387 --> 01:12:41.254
You must have had difficulty
swallowing all those aspros.

01:12:44.793 --> 01:12:49.025
No. I - I just drank them with water.
It wasn't hard.

01:12:49.131 --> 01:12:51.099
They just went down.

01:13:07.516 --> 01:13:10.280
"You have a real talent for writing."

01:13:27.870 --> 01:13:30.338
"You have a real talent
for writing."

01:13:32.141 --> 01:13:34.371
-Janet.
- Yes?

01:13:34.476 --> 01:13:37.343
Three men from the university
to see you.

01:13:45.854 --> 01:13:47.981
Ah.

01:13:48.090 --> 01:13:50.558
- Hello, Janet.
- Evening, Janet.

01:13:50.659 --> 01:13:52.627
- Hello,Janet.
- Hello.

01:13:55.063 --> 01:13:57.258
Uh, Mr. Forrest has been telling me...

01:13:57.366 --> 01:14:00.335
that, uh, you haven't been
feeling all that well lately...

01:14:00.436 --> 01:14:04.133
and, well, we thought
that you might like a little rest.

01:14:05.808 --> 01:14:09.471
Oh. N-No, I'm fine now, thank you.

01:14:09.578 --> 01:14:12.479
Well, i-it wouldn't be for long.
Just, uh -

01:14:12.581 --> 01:14:16.415
Well, just have a little rest
and let us look after you for a while.

01:14:18.253 --> 01:14:20.153
Really, I'm all right.

01:14:20.255 --> 01:14:22.519
John would come to visit you.
Wouldn't you, John?

01:14:22.624 --> 01:14:24.524
Of course I would, yeah.

01:14:24.626 --> 01:14:26.594
In hospital?

01:14:28.030 --> 01:14:31.466
Well, yes, we think
it would be best for you.

01:14:33.769 --> 01:14:36.567
- Do you think so?
- I do.

01:15:30.058 --> 01:15:31.958
Come on, Nini.

01:15:36.231 --> 01:15:38.426
I can't go home.

01:15:38.534 --> 01:15:41.401
- Well, you can't stay here.
- No, I don't want to stay here.

01:15:41.503 --> 01:15:44.199
Well, where can you go?

01:15:44.306 --> 01:15:48.402
Look, after a holiday at home,
you'll be as good as new.

01:15:52.214 --> 01:15:54.512
Go away!

01:15:57.185 --> 01:16:01.986
- She's usually such a happy girl.
- Go away!

01:16:02.090 --> 01:16:04.957
We'd better go.

01:16:06.862 --> 01:16:09.330
Perhaps she just needs a little more rest.

01:16:18.307 --> 01:16:22.641
- I had a little dog -
- And his name was -
- Spot.

01:16:22.744 --> 01:16:25.736
- I had a little dog -
- And his name was -

01:16:25.847 --> 01:16:27.815
- Spot.
- I had a little dog -

01:16:27.916 --> 01:16:30.316
- And his name was -
- Spot.

01:16:30.419 --> 01:16:34.412
- I had a little dog, and his name was -
- Spot.

01:16:34.523 --> 01:16:37.492
- I had a little dog -
- And his name was -

01:16:37.593 --> 01:16:40.255
- Spot.
- I had a little dog -

01:16:40.362 --> 01:16:42.387
- And his name was -
- Spot.

01:16:44.333 --> 01:16:46.301
Here we go again.

01:16:48.303 --> 01:16:50.203
Come back!

01:16:54.309 --> 01:16:57.506
Here we go. Here we go.

01:17:32.180 --> 01:17:34.978
Pits.

01:17:39.921 --> 01:17:42.151
I 've got schizophrenia.

01:17:42.257 --> 01:17:44.157
What's that?

01:17:48.764 --> 01:17:53.133
"Dementia praecox,
otherwise known as schizophrenia.

01:17:53.235 --> 01:17:55.897
"A gradual deterioration of the mind...

01:17:56.004 --> 01:17:57.972
with no cure."

01:18:32.374 --> 01:18:34.365
Janet.

01:18:34.476 --> 01:18:38.776
I've talked to a Mrs. Chandler.
in Christchurch about your case.

01:18:38.880 --> 01:18:41.713
She's very interested in you.

01:18:41.817 --> 01:18:43.876
I think you'll like her too.

01:18:43.985 --> 01:18:46.249
Do you mean
I should go and see her?

01:18:46.354 --> 01:18:48.345
I think you should.

01:18:48.457 --> 01:18:52.553
I've shown your stories and poems
to Denis Glover of Caxton.

01:18:52.661 --> 01:18:54.754
He's very impressed.

01:18:57.365 --> 01:19:01.392
You know, Janet, when I think of you,
I think of van Gogh, Hugo Wolf.

01:19:01.503 --> 01:19:04.131
Lots of artists have suffered
from schizophrenia.

01:19:11.213 --> 01:19:13.647
Bruddie?

01:19:17.953 --> 01:19:20.922
You should be the one going, Nini,
not me.

01:19:22.691 --> 01:19:24.659
Oh, no. I couldn't.

01:19:27.562 --> 01:19:29.587
You'd be the best one.

01:19:29.698 --> 01:19:33.725
Whoever goes, you've got to make sure
Mum has a lovely trip.

01:19:34.770 --> 01:19:38.968
- It's most of my money!

01:19:39.074 --> 01:19:42.237
- No, it's not. It's mostly Janet's money.
- Yeah.

01:19:42.344 --> 01:19:45.802
- No, it's not. I worked for it.
- I earn more money than you do.

01:19:45.914 --> 01:19:47.939
Work for it? Huh.

01:19:50.752 --> 01:19:53.220
Oh, dear, dear, dear.
I don't know.

01:19:53.321 --> 01:19:55.619
-What don't you know?

01:19:55.724 --> 01:19:57.692
Put your feet up.

01:19:57.793 --> 01:20:00.421
- I'm all right.
- Come on.

01:20:01.763 --> 01:20:05.028
There. You're on holidays, Mum.

01:20:05.133 --> 01:20:09.797
Stop worrying.
Poor old trotters.

01:20:21.817 --> 01:20:24.786
- It's mine!

01:20:24.886 --> 01:20:26.786
Hello?

01:20:34.262 --> 01:20:36.162
Yeah.

01:20:36.264 --> 01:20:38.232
Yeah. Okay.

01:20:51.313 --> 01:20:53.281
It's Isabel.

01:20:55.050 --> 01:20:57.746
She drowned in Picton Harbour.

01:21:37.959 --> 01:21:40.484
It's to stop her from smelling.

01:21:45.500 --> 01:21:47.400
Bruddie.

01:21:50.639 --> 01:21:52.607
Mum, your hair - it's white.

01:21:53.708 --> 01:21:55.676
- Oh, Curly!

01:21:55.777 --> 01:21:57.745
A second one taken.

01:22:01.216 --> 01:22:06.119
We just don't know what to say,
but call on us if you want any help.

01:22:06.221 --> 01:22:09.088
- We're here. We're sorry
we didn't come to the church.
- Is Janet coming out?

01:22:09.190 --> 01:22:12.091
We knew you had
closer family and friends...

01:22:12.193 --> 01:22:16.527
and we kept in the background
for that reason.

01:22:19.768 --> 01:22:22.362
Why don't you come out, Nini?

01:22:46.928 --> 01:22:50.557
I comforted myself with writing...

01:22:50.665 --> 01:22:53.862
yet I could not stay at Willowglen...

01:22:53.969 --> 01:22:57.598
nor was there any escape
from the horror of my decayed teeth.

01:23:09.417 --> 01:23:11.681
Hello. Come in.

01:23:16.725 --> 01:23:19.285
- I'm Janet Frame.
- Oh.

01:23:19.394 --> 01:23:21.862
John Forrest wrote to me about you.

01:23:24.299 --> 01:23:26.290
Will you help me with my teeth?

01:23:27.402 --> 01:23:31.361
Your teeth?
I don't understand.

01:23:37.412 --> 01:23:41.041
Oh, dear.

01:23:41.149 --> 01:23:43.982
I'm afraid you're gonna have to
have those out.

01:23:44.085 --> 01:23:45.985
Will you come with me?

01:23:47.288 --> 01:23:49.381
Well, yes, I could.

01:23:56.664 --> 01:23:58.962
After you've had your teeth seen to...

01:23:59.067 --> 01:24:01.592
I'd like you to go
to Sunnyside Hospital.

01:24:01.703 --> 01:24:05.230
They have a new treatment there
which appears to be successful.

01:24:07.442 --> 01:24:09.342
Is it curable?

01:24:09.444 --> 01:24:13.744
With this new treatment,
yes, I think it may be.

01:24:38.873 --> 01:24:42.172
- Nurse?

01:24:51.853 --> 01:24:53.821
You're a newie, aren't you?

01:24:56.558 --> 01:24:58.822
Come on. Legs up.
That's the way. Get yourself comfy.

01:24:58.927 --> 01:25:02.385
- Where are your teeth?
- I've just had them pulled out.

01:25:02.497 --> 01:25:04.863
Ooh.

01:25:07.502 --> 01:25:10.266
- Have you eaten today?

01:25:10.371 --> 01:25:12.396
Oh! Oops-a-day.

01:25:14.008 --> 01:25:17.967
No! There's God! There's God!

01:25:18.079 --> 01:25:20.309
- That's a good girl.
- There's God -

01:25:20.415 --> 01:25:22.440
-All right, Doctor.

01:25:22.550 --> 01:25:26.008
Good morning. Well, then,
we know what this is all about.

01:25:26.121 --> 01:25:28.316
Lie down. That's all right.

01:25:28.423 --> 01:25:30.584
Legs down. Legs down.

01:25:30.692 --> 01:25:32.956
- Nice and calm.
- Matron.

01:25:33.061 --> 01:25:35.962
Yes. Close your eyes.
Ready, Doctor?

01:26:03.424 --> 01:26:05.392
Over the next eightyears...

01:26:05.493 --> 01:26:09.156
I received more than 200 applications
of electric shock treatment...

01:26:10.298 --> 01:26:13.062
each one equivalent in fear.
to an execution.

01:26:38.826 --> 01:26:41.260
Hurry up!

01:26:41.362 --> 01:26:44.490
- On the go.
- Come on. Hurry.

01:26:45.767 --> 01:26:48.497
Are you all right?

01:26:48.603 --> 01:26:50.468
I'm all right.

01:26:56.544 --> 01:26:59.513
- Hurry up.
- I don't want to go while they're watching.

01:27:03.918 --> 01:27:06.716
There's no one watching!

01:27:06.821 --> 01:27:08.789
Come on, go!

01:27:10.291 --> 01:27:12.953
- Miss Educated!
- Yeah.

01:27:27.508 --> 01:27:30.341
- There you are.

01:27:30.445 --> 01:27:32.913
Blue smoke

01:27:33.014 --> 01:27:35.710
Goes drifting by

01:27:35.817 --> 01:27:41.119
Into the deep blue sky

01:27:41.222 --> 01:27:44.487
When I think of home

01:27:44.592 --> 01:27:49.495
I sadly sigh

01:27:49.597 --> 01:27:54.159
Oh, I can see you there

01:27:54.269 --> 01:27:59.605
With loving tears in your eyes

01:27:59.707 --> 01:28:03.507
As we fondly said

01:28:03.611 --> 01:28:07.240
Our last good-byes

01:28:08.816 --> 01:28:12.843
And as I sailed away

01:28:12.954 --> 01:28:16.185
With a longing to stay

01:28:16.291 --> 01:28:21.558
- I promised to be true

01:29:05.540 --> 01:29:08.168
- I've got your books.
- Good work,Janet.

01:29:08.276 --> 01:29:11.541
-Jolly good work.
- They've published them.

01:29:27.562 --> 01:29:31.760
- Where's my photograph?
- That's not the important thing.

01:29:33.000 --> 01:29:36.868
- Wh-Where's my photograph?
- The important thing is that you're an author.

01:29:39.507 --> 01:29:41.839
What do I do?

01:29:43.244 --> 01:29:45.508
You sign it here...

01:29:45.613 --> 01:29:48.081
on the inside front page.

01:29:49.250 --> 01:29:52.549
- Is that what you do?
- Mmm.

01:30:01.529 --> 01:30:03.497
Good. Next one.

01:30:08.202 --> 01:30:10.602
They'll be worth a fortune
one day,Janet.

01:30:19.614 --> 01:30:21.514
Good.

01:30:22.750 --> 01:30:24.650
Sit down.

01:30:33.895 --> 01:30:36.557
We're putting you down
for that new operation.

01:30:40.968 --> 01:30:42.936
What new operation?

01:30:43.037 --> 01:30:45.904
You're going to have a leukotomy.

01:30:48.075 --> 01:30:50.475
There's no need to be frightened.

01:30:50.578 --> 01:30:52.808
It'll do you the world of good.

01:30:55.116 --> 01:30:57.084
Do I have to have one?

01:30:58.920 --> 01:31:02.117
It's not a question of"have to."
It's a question of what's best.

01:31:03.524 --> 01:31:06.459
Your mother has agreed.
She signed the papers.

01:31:30.418 --> 01:31:32.386
What do you think?

01:31:33.521 --> 01:31:36.547
Do you think they'll get out?

01:31:36.657 --> 01:31:40.559
I think once you're here,
you never get out.

01:32:09.624 --> 01:32:13.651
Fear... no... more...

01:32:14.729 --> 01:32:16.663
the heat...

01:32:16.764 --> 01:32:20.097
of the sun...

01:32:21.469 --> 01:32:26.338
nor the furious...

01:32:26.440 --> 01:32:29.170
winter's...

01:32:29.277 --> 01:32:31.677
rages.

01:32:31.779 --> 01:32:34.680
Now thy...

01:32:34.782 --> 01:32:39.048
worldly... task...

01:32:39.153 --> 01:32:41.519
is done.

01:32:51.432 --> 01:32:53.457
Oh. Hello.

01:32:53.568 --> 01:32:56.594
-Janet, isn't it?
- Dr. Palmer, what do you think?

01:32:56.704 --> 01:33:01.266
- About the prize?
- No. About the leukotomy.

01:33:01.375 --> 01:33:04.606
You've won the Hubert Church Award...

01:33:04.712 --> 01:33:07.579
for your book of short stories,
The Lagoon.

01:33:09.717 --> 01:33:14.086
Oh. I'm not going
to have the operation?

01:33:14.188 --> 01:33:16.088
No.

01:33:16.190 --> 01:33:18.658
I think you should stay in hospital
a little longer....

01:33:18.759 --> 01:33:22.126
until you're more confident
and stronger..

01:33:22.229 --> 01:33:25.130
And then we'll see
about getting you home.

01:34:11.112 --> 01:34:13.080
Seacliff Station, please.

01:35:02.263 --> 01:35:05.130
I don't want you
to leave home again ever.

01:35:07.835 --> 01:35:09.735
Okay, chief.

01:35:14.008 --> 01:35:18.308
- You're not going back to that nuthouse.
- With all those loonies?

01:35:19.447 --> 01:35:21.574
Aw, Dad.

01:35:21.682 --> 01:35:24.651
It's my private rest home
you're talking about.

01:35:31.058 --> 01:35:33.026
Why don't you eat with us?

01:35:39.100 --> 01:35:41.728
Why don't you live
in your own house?

01:35:43.104 --> 01:35:45.072
Have you got any children?

01:35:46.640 --> 01:35:49.268
Boys, come on.
Leave Auntie Janet alone, please.

01:35:49.376 --> 01:35:51.606
- Come have your tea.
- All right.

01:35:51.712 --> 01:35:53.612
Come on.

01:35:55.416 --> 01:35:58.180
Can you see something
out the window? Out.

01:35:58.285 --> 01:36:01.743
Frank Sargeson, the writer,
lives around here in an old bach.

01:36:03.023 --> 01:36:06.720
He came to visit me.
He heard I was your sister.

01:36:06.827 --> 01:36:09.887
- He asked if you'd like to go and see him.
- We could drop in now.

01:36:09.997 --> 01:36:13.899
No! I don't know him.

01:36:23.978 --> 01:36:25.946
He's not home.

01:36:27.515 --> 01:36:30.609
- Hello.
- You're Janet Frame?

01:36:30.718 --> 01:36:33.186
Come in. Come in.

01:36:34.488 --> 01:36:36.456
We'll come back later.

01:36:43.097 --> 01:36:45.895
Why don't you come and live here?

01:36:46.000 --> 01:36:49.458
There's a bed and desk
in the hut out back already set up.

01:36:50.871 --> 01:36:53.738
Well, you can't write
living in suburbia...

01:36:54.975 --> 01:36:58.172
amongst the nappies
and the bourgeois life.

01:36:59.547 --> 01:37:01.572
But I have to find a job.

01:37:01.682 --> 01:37:04.310
Why?

01:37:04.418 --> 01:37:06.386
You're a writer.

01:37:08.656 --> 01:37:10.749
They've refused me
the sickness benefit.

01:37:10.858 --> 01:37:12.883
Oh, have they?

01:37:12.993 --> 01:37:16.588
After all those years in hospital,
they can't do that.

01:37:18.966 --> 01:37:21.161
Look, I've got a good friend
who's a doctor.

01:37:21.268 --> 01:37:24.601
He'll fix you up with a benefit.
Of course he will.

01:37:26.040 --> 01:37:28.508
Would you like to come and look?

01:38:16.323 --> 01:38:18.257
"It was a sin...

01:38:18.359 --> 01:38:22.295
"to have watched Aunt Nettie
putting on her face...

01:38:22.396 --> 01:38:24.694
- "and it was worse -
- No, don't.

01:38:24.798 --> 01:38:26.925
- "it was worse for her, I suppose...
- Frank!

01:38:27.034 --> 01:38:30.470
"because now we knew
she had another face...

01:38:30.571 --> 01:38:32.801
- "and had another smile to it.
- Frank!

01:38:32.907 --> 01:38:35.774
"We'd found her out like a thief.

01:38:35.876 --> 01:38:38.344
She kept blushing."

01:38:41.949 --> 01:38:44.417
Not bad.

01:38:44.518 --> 01:38:47.715
Bit... Dylan Thomas-ish.

01:38:51.892 --> 01:38:55.020
Don't worry I fit comes back.
