02:09:22.488 --> 02:09:25.355
My girl, who can play the Maori
stick game from New Zealand...

02:09:25.457 --> 02:09:28.756
can also drink wine and kiss
at the same time.

02:09:28.861 --> 02:09:33.059
- She can chug at the same time?
- Chug-a-lug.

02:09:33.165 --> 02:09:35.429
Chug, chug, chug.

02:09:35.534 --> 02:09:37.434
Look at that.
Now, that is the sort -

02:09:37.536 --> 02:09:39.504
You're always showing off, Bernard.
I'm sick of it.

02:09:39.605 --> 02:09:42.631
I'm always showing off?
Come on! En garde!

02:09:44.710 --> 02:09:46.678
- You always go too far!

02:09:46.779 --> 02:09:48.679
Someone get this guy off me.

02:10:08.333 --> 02:10:11.666
I haven't heard your typewriter for weeks.
You're not writing, are you?

02:10:14.106 --> 02:10:16.006
I'm taking a break.

02:10:17.476 --> 02:10:19.944
I hope you know what you're doing.

02:10:23.015 --> 02:10:25.142
- Of course I do.
- Okay.

02:11:17.069 --> 02:11:19.333
Well, I guess this is my last week.

02:11:24.209 --> 02:11:26.677
Oh, come on.
You knew I was going.

02:11:27.713 --> 02:11:29.772
No.

02:11:29.882 --> 02:11:33.579
Well, I have to get back,
prepare for next term and so on.

02:11:33.685 --> 02:11:36.677
God knows, I don't want to go.

02:11:36.788 --> 02:11:38.756
I didn't realize it was next week.

02:11:38.857 --> 02:11:43.294
Hey, listen. Look. No, no, no.
Listen to me.

02:11:45.264 --> 02:11:47.459
I've had a great summer.

02:11:48.901 --> 02:11:50.869
I really mean that.

02:11:52.404 --> 02:11:54.372
I'm gonna miss you.

02:11:56.375 --> 02:11:58.605
Huh?

02:11:58.710 --> 02:12:00.610
Hmm?

02:12:27.272 --> 02:12:30.730
Francesca.
Senorita Janetta - is she home?

02:12:37.549 --> 02:12:39.744
Look, I love you too.

02:12:46.391 --> 02:12:48.621
- Janet?

02:12:54.132 --> 02:12:56.760
-Janet? Are you there?

02:13:02.908 --> 02:13:05.240
Uh, the ferry goes at midday.

02:13:09.815 --> 02:13:11.715
Janet?

02:13:19.958 --> 02:13:22.426
I'd really like to say good-bye.

02:13:58.830 --> 02:14:01.230
Janetta?

02:14:08.907 --> 02:14:11.535
These Americans,
they spoil everything.

02:14:11.643 --> 02:14:17.343
Even the light they make dark.

02:14:53.685 --> 02:14:55.653
True romance, indeed.

02:14:55.754 --> 02:14:57.984
So much for poetry and music.

02:14:58.090 --> 02:15:01.218
I was beginning to suspect
that I might be pregnant.

02:15:03.562 --> 02:15:06.360
Here.

02:15:06.465 --> 02:15:09.491
Here. What you got in here?

02:15:12.170 --> 02:15:15.298
I managed to get you a room
in the main house...

02:15:15.407 --> 02:15:17.739
next to mine.

02:15:17.843 --> 02:15:20.311
Oh, we've got a new landlady.

02:15:20.412 --> 02:15:23.176
She's a real character.
Tip-top.

02:15:23.281 --> 02:15:25.249
She likes to be called Ma.

02:15:27.319 --> 02:15:29.378
By the way...

02:15:29.488 --> 02:15:31.956
I trust you're still fancy-free.

02:15:35.627 --> 02:15:37.822
Great. Come on then!

02:15:37.929 --> 02:15:40.022
I've got some tea on.

02:15:40.132 --> 02:15:43.101
It's the bus!
Janet! Where are you?

02:15:52.244 --> 02:15:54.838
You don't want to spend
your time writing.

02:15:56.915 --> 02:15:58.883
There's no money in it.

02:16:02.654 --> 02:16:05.054
It's all right for a holiday...

02:16:05.157 --> 02:16:07.717
but nothin' else.

02:16:07.826 --> 02:16:09.794
Not for permanent.

02:16:16.301 --> 02:16:18.792
What about Peek Freans?

02:16:20.739 --> 02:16:23.299
- Peek Freans?
- Yeah!

02:16:23.408 --> 02:16:26.206
You could work in the office there.

02:16:27.412 --> 02:16:29.312
Yeah!

02:17:17.662 --> 02:17:20.290
Although I had not wanted the baby...

02:17:20.397 --> 02:17:23.959
I had sometimes imagined
a boy with Bernard's laugh...

02:17:24.068 --> 02:17:26.434
or a girl with his eyes.

02:17:29.608 --> 02:17:32.906
So nice to have a mature applicant.

02:17:33.011 --> 02:17:35.478
We have so many young ones.

02:17:38.650 --> 02:17:40.674
Any major illnesses?

02:17:40.785 --> 02:17:42.684
No.

02:17:42.787 --> 02:17:46.587
- Uh, any operations?
- No.

02:17:46.691 --> 02:17:49.455
- Psychiatric treatment?
- Yes.

02:17:51.129 --> 02:17:53.995
I spent some time in hospital
in New Zealand.

02:17:54.099 --> 02:17:56.431
How long is "some time"?

02:17:58.403 --> 02:18:00.303
Eight years.

02:18:00.405 --> 02:18:03.532
How could you possibly think
of being a nurse?

02:18:06.477 --> 02:18:08.446
What was the diagnosis?

02:18:13.885 --> 02:18:16.752
- Schizophrenia.
- I'm sorry.

02:18:16.855 --> 02:18:19.483
No.

02:18:19.591 --> 02:18:22.321
It's out of the question.

02:19:01.665 --> 02:19:04.294
I felt as if all the griefs I had ever known...

02:19:04.402 --> 02:19:07.303
were beginning to surface within me.

02:19:15.980 --> 02:19:18.574
In fear and despair for my life...

02:19:18.683 --> 02:19:23.643
I needed answers to the questions
I still asked myself about my history.

02:19:23.754 --> 02:19:28.215
I knew that talk ofsuicide
must always be taken seriously.

02:19:28.325 --> 02:19:32.592
Such talk came readily to me
as a shortcut to ensure action.

02:19:38.202 --> 02:19:40.831
I was admitted
as a voluntary patient.

02:20:23.248 --> 02:20:27.207
Finally it was concluded that I had
never suffered from schizophrenia.

02:20:28.253 --> 02:20:31.279
At first the tr.uth seemed
mor.e ter.r.ifying than the lie.

02:20:32.657 --> 02:20:36.286
How could I now ask for help
when there was nothing wrong with me?

02:20:39.230 --> 02:20:41.596
You know the problems
you've been experiencing...

02:20:41.699 --> 02:20:44.691
are a direct result
of all those years in hospital.

02:20:44.803 --> 02:20:47.271
You can't undo that quickly.

02:20:47.372 --> 02:20:49.772
I'm here whenever you need me...

02:20:49.874 --> 02:20:54.038
but, I think for a start,
once a week.

02:20:54.145 --> 02:20:56.045
Once a week. All right.

02:20:56.147 --> 02:21:01.346
Mmm. And I want you to write about
your time spent in hospital in New Zealand.

02:21:01.453 --> 02:21:05.719
It'll help give you
a clearer view to the future.

02:21:05.824 --> 02:21:08.987
- But I have to find a job.
- Don't have to worry about that.

02:21:09.093 --> 02:21:11.618
You'll get National Assistance.

02:21:11.729 --> 02:21:14.857
If anyone tells you to get out and mix...

02:21:14.966 --> 02:21:17.298
and you don't want to...

02:21:17.402 --> 02:21:19.302
don't.

02:22:37.248 --> 02:22:40.615
- Have you read it?
- Yes, I have.

02:22:40.718 --> 02:22:44.381
And I'm sure that getting that time
out of your system will be good for you.

02:22:46.424 --> 02:22:49.985
But as a book, do you like it?

02:22:50.094 --> 02:22:53.063
I told you, I 'm not a literary chap.

02:22:54.265 --> 02:22:56.495
Have you thought of getting an agent?

02:22:56.601 --> 02:22:59.092
- I already have one.
- What did he say?

02:22:59.203 --> 02:23:03.003
- I wanted you to read it first.
- That's good.

02:23:04.275 --> 02:23:07.733
Now I have, take it to him,
get his opinion.

02:23:58.529 --> 02:24:01.327
I'm going to meet
my publisher tomorrow.

02:24:01.432 --> 02:24:05.232
Ooh! Why don't I make
a hair appointment for you?

02:24:05.336 --> 02:24:08.703
Oh, no. Nothing works. I've tried.

02:24:12.844 --> 02:24:15.312
I'm sure they could
do something with it.

02:24:30.628 --> 02:24:33.859
Granted, your books
have had good reviews.

02:24:33.965 --> 02:24:35.990
Some very good.

02:24:36.100 --> 02:24:39.729
But what I want you to do now
is write a best seller.

02:24:42.106 --> 02:24:46.202
When Wanda Lyons comes to see me,
do you know how she comes?

02:24:46.310 --> 02:24:48.778
She comes in a Rolls-Royce.

02:24:48.880 --> 02:24:51.508
You are a better writer
than Wanda.

02:24:53.751 --> 02:24:55.651
Best seller.

02:24:55.753 --> 02:24:57.721
Best seller.

02:24:57.822 --> 02:25:00.290
Study them.
They'll give you the form.

02:25:01.793 --> 02:25:04.261
- Where is it you're living?
- Camberwell.

02:25:04.362 --> 02:25:07.388
Camberwell is a wasteland.

02:25:07.498 --> 02:25:11.093
I'll make you an offer.
I'll give you an apartment.

02:25:11.202 --> 02:25:13.796
Give me?

02:25:13.905 --> 02:25:16.635
Yes, I'd like you to write
your next book in there.

02:25:19.977 --> 02:25:23.913
Uh - I don't know.
I'll have to see.

02:25:24.015 --> 02:25:28.111
Also, I've got some people
who'd like to meet you.

02:25:29.954 --> 02:25:31.854
And don't forget.

02:25:31.956 --> 02:25:34.652
Next time you come
in a Rolls-Royce.

02:26:05.156 --> 02:26:08.284
There. These should fit you as well.

02:26:08.392 --> 02:26:11.190
Lovely. Now, I'll send Columba
for your wet things.

02:26:11.295 --> 02:26:15.061
Oh, I loved your last book.
It was just absolutely marvelous.

02:26:15.166 --> 02:26:17.464
- Take your time.
- Thank you.

02:26:36.921 --> 02:26:39.389
- You enjoyed the book then?
- Oh,yes.

02:26:39.490 --> 02:26:42.323
She's an interesting new author..

02:26:42.426 --> 02:26:45.486
Probably won't sell.
It probably won't be a best seller..

02:26:45.596 --> 02:26:47.928
We won't lose anything on it.

02:26:48.032 --> 02:26:50.899
Janet Frame,
Alan and Ruth Sillitoe.

02:26:51.002 --> 02:26:53.027
- Pleased to meet you at last.
- I 'll get you a drink.

02:26:53.137 --> 02:26:55.105
- Hello.
-Janet, welcome.

02:26:55.206 --> 02:26:58.175
Janet, do make yourself comfortable.
Sit down, please.

02:27:01.179 --> 02:27:03.443
I loved your Faces in the Water..

02:27:03.548 --> 02:27:05.948
It's powerful stuff.
Very true.

02:27:08.085 --> 02:27:09.985
Thank you.

02:27:11.889 --> 02:27:15.188
I, um - I enjoyed your book too.

02:27:15.293 --> 02:27:17.386
The Loneliness
of the Long-Distance Runner..

02:27:19.197 --> 02:27:21.097
I 'm glad.

02:27:23.234 --> 02:27:25.259
Here you are,Janet.

02:27:25.369 --> 02:27:27.269
Thank you.

02:27:31.876 --> 02:27:36.472
Janet's in our Knightsbridge
apartment at the moment...

02:27:36.581 --> 02:27:38.811
writing her new book.

02:27:38.916 --> 02:27:40.816
Yes.

02:27:49.060 --> 02:27:50.960
I am.

02:28:12.416 --> 02:28:14.543
Dear Janet...

02:28:14.652 --> 02:28:17.678
I wish there was a way
to break this news more gently.

02:28:19.090 --> 02:28:21.422
Dad is dead.

02:28:21.525 --> 02:28:26.155
He was cycling to work on the North Road
when he collapsed and died later in hospital.

02:28:27.932 --> 02:28:32.562
Poor Dad. He hasn 't properly
cared for himself since Mum died.

02:28:32.670 --> 02:28:35.366
Bruddie says the house
is a rubbish heap.

02:31:15.433 --> 02:31:17.333
Miss Frame?

02:31:19.203 --> 02:31:22.297
Ken Bowker
from the local paper, Miss Frame.

02:31:22.406 --> 02:31:24.374
Can we come up?

02:31:27.845 --> 02:31:29.745
Yes.

02:31:47.131 --> 02:31:51.033
Sorry to disturb you.
We wanted to beat the Dunedin papers to it.

02:31:53.637 --> 02:31:56.231
- To what?
- Your story.

02:31:58.476 --> 02:32:00.603
Can you bend your knees?

02:32:07.885 --> 02:32:10.183
Can we have one sitting,
Miss Frame?

02:32:10.287 --> 02:32:12.187
Sitting.

02:32:15.893 --> 02:32:19.420
Um - Like this?

02:32:21.165 --> 02:32:23.497
That's good.

02:32:34.678 --> 02:32:37.374
Come on, baby

02:32:37.481 --> 02:32:39.972
Let's do the twist

02:32:41.018 --> 02:32:43.816
Come on, baby

02:32:43.921 --> 02:32:46.116
Let's do the twist

02:32:46.223 --> 02:32:49.249
- Pamela, come to bed, please?
- Take me by my little hand

02:32:50.427 --> 02:32:53.157
And go like this

02:32:53.264 --> 02:32:55.755
- Coffee?
- Uh, no thanks,June.

02:32:56.800 --> 02:32:58.700
- See you tomorrow then.
- Night-night.

02:32:58.802 --> 02:33:03.501
- Night-night.
- Ooh, yeah

02:33:03.607 --> 02:33:06.041
Just like this

02:33:06.143 --> 02:33:08.839
Come on, little girl

02:33:09.880 --> 02:33:11.848
And do the twist

02:33:13.050 --> 02:33:16.042
My daddy is sleepin'

02:33:16.153 --> 02:33:18.781
And my mama ain't around

02:33:18.889 --> 02:33:22.256
Yes, Daddy's just sleepin'

02:33:22.359 --> 02:33:24.293
And Mama ain't around

02:33:31.802 --> 02:33:34.828
Yeah, now twist

02:33:34.939 --> 02:33:38.397
Girl, baby, twist

02:33:38.509 --> 02:33:42.036
Ooh, yeah

02:33:42.146 --> 02:33:45.240
Just like this

02:33:45.349 --> 02:33:48.079
Come on, little miss

02:33:48.185 --> 02:33:50.176
And do the twist

02:34:06.503 --> 02:34:09.404
Hush, hush, hush.

02:34:10.808 --> 02:34:13.641
The grass and the wind...

02:34:13.744 --> 02:34:15.644
and the fir...

02:34:15.746 --> 02:34:17.873
and the sea are saying...

02:34:19.049 --> 02:34:20.983
hush...

02:34:21.085 --> 02:34:23.645
hush...

02:34:23.754 --> 02:34:25.654
hush.

